- Sum of digits is $2+1=3$, so divisible by 3? Let's check: $2^{64} \equiv (-1)^{64} \equiv 1 \pmod{3}$, so $2^{64} + 1 \equiv 1 + 1 \equiv 2 \pmod{3}$. Not divisible by 3
