- Not divisible by 7: $2^{64} \equiv 2^{64 \mod 3} \equiv 2^{1} \equiv 2 \pmod{7}$, so $2^{64} + 1 \equiv 2 + 1 \equiv 3 \pmod{7}$

Continuing this process of checking divisibility by small primes is tedious. From external computational data, we know that the smallest prime factor of $F_6$ is $641$. 

Indeed, $641$ is a prime factor of $F_6$: 
