The definition of $a(n)$ is equivalent to the closed form:
$$a(n) = 2^n - \lfloor \log_2(P_n) \rfloor$$
where $P_n = \operatorname{minFac}(\operatorname{fermatNumber} n)$.
The subtraction is defined in $\mathbb{N}$ and is safe
